### Example of a cross-platform compatible font-stack

```css
body {
    font-family: 
        BlinkMacSystemFont,
        'Segoe UI',
        Roboto,
        Oxygen-Sans,
        Ubuntu,
        Cantarell,
        'Helvetica Neue',
        sans-serif !important;
}
```


### HTML 

If using the GOV.UK Prototype Kit, replace the content inside the <code>{% block header %}</code> block in the with the following HTML.

```html
<header class="govuk-header app-header" role="banner" data-module="govuk-header">
   <div class="govuk-header__container govuk-width-container">
    <div class="govuk-header__logo">
      <a href="/" class="govuk-header__link govuk-header__link--homepage">
      <span class="govuk-header__logotype">
         <img src="/public/images/crest.png" alt="Department for Education homepage" class="govuk-header__logotype-crown-fallback-image">
          <span class="govuk-header__logotype-text">
            Department for Education
          </span>
        </span>
        <span class="govuk-header__product-name">
          Service name
        </span>
      </a>     
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

```

### SCSS content to style the header

This is just for prototypes, we are working on a DfE branded header component which can be implements into services more easily. 

```scss

$dfe-blue: #003a69;
$accent: #347ca9;


.govuk-header {
    background-color: $dfe-blue;
}

.govuk-header__container {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: -10px;
    padding-top: 25px;
    padding-bottom: 15px;
    border-bottom: 10px solid $accent;
}

.govuk-header__product-name, .govuk-header__logotype-text {
    line-height: 2.5rem !important;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
}

.govuk-header__logotype-crown-fallback-image{height: 45px; width: 45px;}

```

### Crest logo

You must not use the GOV.UK Crown logotype on services not provided on GOV.UK or services.gov.uk. Instead, use the department crest.

If using the GOV.UK Prototype Kit, download the following crest file and save it to your <code>/app/assets/images</code> folder, and make sure it's named <code>crest.png</code>

The crest image is white on a transparent background, so for display purposes is shown on the blue background.

<a href="/images/crest.png" target="_blank">

<img src="/images/crest.png" height="50px" width="50px" style="background: #003a69; padding: 20px;" alt="crest logo">

